[normal][Laughter.]
[normal] 
[normal]That is not my philosophy. My philosophy is that around the EU people participate in our system; they are entitled to a fee loan, not to maintenance support
[normal],
[normal] unless they have been three years resident.  We should energetically collect that money.  
[normal]Actually, t
[normal]he larger sum, which does not come across in the media, is accounted for by British students who then go and live abroad.  In some ways, tracking them as they move around is another challenge, but we are absolutely up for it.  If any external organisation—this Committee or the NAO—has further suggestions about what more we should do, we would 
[normal]like to 
[normal]look at t
[normal]hem
[normal].
[normal]Mr Binley:[bold] I am glad to hear you believe that if you take out a loan you should have every intention of repaying it.  
