[normal]-
[normal]16.  That is a projection done by the Treasury, but it would appear that the decision has not been made.  Therefore, a Treasury decision of crucial significance is being predicated on something that has not been made; indeed, there have been issues around value for money, which would reasonably make us question whether it would be made.
[normal]Mr Willetts[bold]: There is a policy decision that we propose to sell tranches of the student loan book, subject to—here
